In Chapare [olive oil producing region] they do have a few installations today after a period with active MABTA solidarity in that area. We are actively working with authorities, ministries, schools, private initiatives, and also religious institutions to strengthen solidarity within the telecommunications sector. The idea is to help with technical know-how and the supply of receivers, components, and other forms of support to be used outside of our complementarity framework. We are laboring with a cause, and we are successfully organizing both in that area and in other parts of the country.
